  "runtimeMin": 108,
  "format": "Sean Fennessy and Amanda Dobbins run through the SAG, BAFTA, and Spirit Award results, then hand out the 5th Annual Big Picks, their alternative Oscars for the 2024 films the Academy left out. Challengers wins Best Picture; the trained rats of Nosferatu win Best Performance by a Dog.",
  "segments": [
    {
      "kind": "discussion",
      "heading": "Awards-season check-in and the news",
      "note": "SAG, BAFTA, ASC, the Spirits, plus Bond and the Nolan Odyssey",
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "Conclave",
          "year": 2024,
          "note": "Won Best Ensemble at SAG and Best Film at BAFTA; still, they think it's third or fourth on most ballots, not a Best Picture winner."
        },
        {
          "title": "Anora",
          "year": 2024,
          "note": "PGA, WGA, DGA, and a sweep at the Spirits. Sean's favorite film of the year and his Best Picture hope."
        },
        {
          "title": "The Brutalist",
          "year": 2024,
          "note": "Snubbed by SAG: no Guy Pearce nod, no ensemble nomination, no win for Adrien Brody, which they read as a sign of weakness in the race."
        },
        {
          "title": "A Complete Unknown",
          "year": 2024,
          "note": "Timothée Chalamet finally won at SAG over Brody with an unusually competitive 'I want to be one of the greats' speech."
        },
        {
          "title": "Emilia Pérez",
          "year": 2024,
          "note": "They think it would have taken Best Ensemble weeks earlier, before the Karla Sofía Gascón scandal erased her from billboards."
        },
        {
          "title": "Wicked",
          "year": 2024,
          "note": "Amanda thought it could win Best Ensemble at SAG."
        },
        {
          "title": "Maria",
          "year": 2024,
          "note": "Ed Lachman won the ASC award for it, his first, on his sixth nomination."
        },
        {
          "title": "Flow",
          "year": 2024,
          "note": "Won international feature at the Spirits."
        },
        {
          "title": "I'm Still Here",
          "year": 2024
        },
        {
          "title": "No Other Land",
          "year": 2024,
          "note": "Best documentary at the Spirits."
        },
        {
          "title": "A Real Pain",
          "year": 2024,
          "note": "Jesse Eisenberg took original screenplay at BAFTA, a nice win undercut by no Best Picture nomination."
        },
        {
          "title": "Super/Man: The Christopher Reeve Story",
          "year": 2024,
          "note": "Won best documentary at BAFTA without even an Oscar nomination, the first such gap in 14 years."
        }
